-- Iceland’s Landsvirkjun Signs ISK 10.5 Billion Revolving Credit
-- B y   L o u i s e   M e e s o n
-- 2011-12-30T15:47:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-30/iceland-s-landsvirkjun-signs-isk-10-5-billion-revolving-credit.html
Landsvirkjun, Iceland’s state-owned
electrical utility, has obtained a 10.5 billion kronur ($86
million)  credit line .  The three-year revolving facility, which can be extended to
as long as five years, is in addition to another $200 million
credit obtained on Dec. 27 and will give the company access to
liquidity “if other conventional funding sources shut down
temporarily”, according to a company statement distributed
today by Globe Newswire  Arion Banki HF, Islandsbanki HF and Landsbanki Islands HF
led and arranged the deal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Louise Meeson in  London  on 
 lmeeson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Faris Khan at 
 Fkhan33@bloomberg.net . 